description.narrative:
1.Notification rate of new ss+ TB cases: New smear positive TB, cases notified to the National Health authorities   during a specified period  per 100 000 population;

2.Treatment success rate: new smear positive TB cases; new smear positive TB cases successfully treated ( cured plus completed) among new smear positive TB cases notified;

3.Notification rate of all forms of TB cases: TB cases (all forms) notified to the national health authorities during a specified period per 100 000 population.

4.Treatment success rate, laboratory confirmed  New MDR-TB cases: laboratory confirmed new MDR TB cases successfully treated ( cured plus completed)  among those enrolled in second-line treatment during  the year of assessment

comment.narrative:
1) TB I-3: TB mortality rate (per 100,000 population): 3.4;
2) TB I-4: MDR-TB prevalence among new TB patients: 15%;
3) TB O-1a: Case notification rate of all forms of TB per 100,000 population - bacteriologically confirmed plus clinically diagnosed, new and relapse cases: 55.9;
4) TB O-1b: Case notification rate per 100,000 population- bacteriologically-confirmed TB, new and relapse-27.2;
5) TB O-2a: Treatment success rate - all forms of TB- 80% 
2015 Cohort;
6) TB O-3: Notification of RR-TB and/or MDR-TB cases - Percentage of notified cases of bacteriologically confirmed, drug resistant RR-TB and/or MDR-TB⃰ as a proportion of the estimated number of RR-TB and/or MDR-TB cases among notified TB cases- 65%;
7) TB O-4: Treatment success rate of MDR-TB: Percentage of bacteriologically confirmed drug resistant TB cases (RR-TB and/or MDR-TB) successfully treated- 60%  Cohort 2013;

