description.narrative:
-National Human Rights Action Plan approved;
-National Institute of Democracy and Human Rights under the President of Turkmenistan  effectively monitors Turkmenistan's international obligations in the sphere of human rights, National Human Rights Action Plan and Universal Periodic Review  implementation and efficiently exercises its mandate;
-Awareness of goverment bodies, public organizations, general public about human rights. Public organizations take part in discussions on National Human Rights Action Plan implementation. Capacity of national trainers strengthened.
-Recomendations of options for National (Representative) Offices for Human Rights/National Representatives for Human Rights prepared.

comment.narrative:
-National Human Rights Action Plan in development;
-Existing/current capacity National Institute of Democracy and Human Rights;
-Limited awareness of public and goverment officials about human rights and regarding Turkmenistan's international obligations in the field of human rights.
-Limited experience in the field of National (Representative) Offices for Human Rights/National Representatives for Human Rights and in the area of constitutional reforms in Turkmenistan

-NHRAP’s implementation is  on schedule. Draft of Monitoring and Evaluation Framework  is developed and agreed with stakeholders;
-Strengthened capacity of Civil Service Organizations. Dialogue between the Government and CSOs is established ;
-Increased awareness of public and government officials on human rights and in respect of Turkmenistan’s obligations increased;
-International experience of reporting on Periodic Report on Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights is researched, recommendations prepared.  Quality National Report is prepared.

-Consultations on designing a unified M&E system for existing NAPs in the area of human rights were held with involvement of two international experts for the Inter-department Committee and the Working Group in November. Recommendations on Guiding Principles on establishment of the National M&E system were presented to the Government for approval.
A draft of the Monitoring and Tracking Tool of NHRAP was developed by the IT for approbation by the national partners;
-A joint seminar on “Development of Civil Society in Turkmenistan” with EU – Central Asia Rule of Law Platform  for 40 people was organized in May. Two UNDP international experts made their presentation at the seminar.
A new initiative on engaging with local civil society organizations was launched. A small assessment of the needs of existing public organizations was carried out.  A database of the active public associations was developed. A capacity building seminar with an international expert on financial sustainability of public associations was held in October. A joint seminar with ICNL for the representatives of the public associations on «Legal and financial aspects of sustainability of public organization in Turkmenistan» was held. 
A dialogue between the Government and the public associations was promoted though organization of a two-day Round table with participation of 50 people, representatives of the Mejlis, line ministries and CSOs from Ashgabat and velayats. A web-portal for CSOs was developed: http://ngo-turkmenistan.org/ ;
-Public launch with presentation of adopted NHRAP was held with participation of senior the senior level of ministries and national agencies, ambassadors and senior diplomats from the development partners’ community, public associations (NGOs) and UN agencies. Publication of NHRAP in Turkmen, Russian and English in 300 copies was printed to be disseminated among different stakeholders including Turkmenistan missions abroad. 7 Press articles published on UNDP website and

